      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can almost imagine the chaos of Heathrow. It's a bit like a war zone, isn't it? But, you know, in the midst of all that chaos, you can actually find a way to stay focused. I'd recommend taking a moment to calm down, grab a cup of coffee, and sit down in a quiet spot to think clearly. You can also try using noise-cancelling headphones or listening to calming music to block out the distractions.\n\nAs for staying focused, try to think of your flight search like a puzzle. You're looking for the right pieces to fit together, and you need to prioritize what's most important. In this case, that's finding a good route to Singapore. You can also try breaking down your search into smaller tasks, like comparing prices or checking layovers, and tackle each one at a time. This can help you stay on track and avoid feeling overwhelmed.\n\nAnd, just like how a skilled navigator uses landmarks and maps to navigate through uncharted territory, you can use your own \"map\" of flight options to find the best route. Keep your priorities in mind, and you'll be well on your way to finding a good flight.",
